        "contentType": "VIDEO",
        "title": "Dow spikes by over 1,300, oil prices retreat in ceasefire rally",
        "description": "<p>All three of the major indexes (<a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"\" class=\"link\" href=\"https://finance.yahoo.com/quote/%5EDJI?p=%5EDJI&.tsrc=fin-srch\" data-i13n=\"slk:^DJI;cpos:1;pos:1\">^DJI</a>, <a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"\" class=\"link\" href=\"https://finance.yahoo.com/quote/%5EIXIC?p=%5EIXIC&.tsrc=fin-srch\" data-i13n=\"slk:^IXIC;cpos:2;pos:1\">^IXIC</a>, <a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"\" class=\"link\" href=\"https://finance.yahoo.com/quote/%5EGSPC?p=%5EGSPC&.tsrc=fin-srch\" data-i13n=\"slk:^GSPC;cpos:3;pos:1\">^GSPC</a>) closed Wednesday's session with colossal gains — the Dow Jones Industrial Average skyrocketed by over 1,320 points (2.85%) and the Nasdaq Composite surged by nearly 620 points (2.8%) — after President Trump announced that Iran agreed to a two-week ceasefire last night.</p>\n<p>Yahoo Finance Markets and Data Editor Jared Blikre takes a closer look at the trading day's biggest sector gainers.</p>",
